\details{
The metadata was collected from the Bioconductor package \code{cellxgenedp}.
\code{vignette("using_cellxgenedp", package="cellxgenedp")} provides an overview of the columns in the
metadata. The data for which the column \code{organism_name} included "Homo
sapiens" was collected collected from \code{cellxgenedp}.

The columns \code{dataset_id} and \code{file_id_cellNexus_single_cell} link the datasets explorable through
\code{cellNexus} and \code{cellxgenedp}to the CELLxGENE portal.

Our representation, harmonises the metadata at dataset, sample and cell
levels, in a unique coherent database table.

Field definitions for the CELLxGENE schema follow the
\href{https://github.com/chanzuckerberg/single-cell-curation/blob/main/schema/5.1.0/schema.md}{CELLxGENE schema 5.1.0}.

Dataset-specific columns:
\code{dataset_id}, \code{collection_id}, \code{citation}, \code{dataset_version_id},
\code{explorer_url}, \code{filesize}, \code{filetype}, \code{published_at}, \code{raw_data_location},
\code{revised_at}, \code{schema_version}, \code{suspension_type}, \code{title}, \code{url}, \code{donor_id}

Sample-specific columns:
\code{assay}, \code{assay_ontology_term_id}, \code{development_stage},
\code{development_stage_ontology_term_id}, \code{self_reported_ethnicity},
\code{self_reported_ethnicity_ontology_term_id}, \code{experiment___}, \code{organism},
\code{organism_ontology_term_id}, \code{sex}, \code{sex_ontology_term_id}, \code{tissue},
\code{tissue_type}, \code{tissue_ontology_term_id}, \code{disease}, \code{disease_ontology_term_id}, \code{is_primary_data}

Cell-specific columns
\code{cell_id}, \code{cell_type}, \code{cell_type_ontology_term_id}, \code{observation_joinid}

Through harmonisation and curation we introduced custom columns not present
in the original CELLxGENE metadata:

\code{cell_count}: Number of cells in a dataset.
\code{feature_count}: Number of genes in a dataset.
\code{age_days}: Donor age in days.
\code{tissue_groups}: Coarse tissue grouping for analysis.
\code{empty_droplet}: Whether a cell is called an empty droplet from expressed-gene count per sample (default threshold 200; targeted panels may differ).
\code{alive}: Whether a cell passes viability / mitochondrial QC.
\code{scDblFinder.class}: Doublet, singlet, or unknown (\code{scDblFinder} default parameters).
\code{cell_type_unified_ensemble}: Consensus immune identity from Azimuth and SingleR (Blueprint, Monaco).
\code{cell_annotation_azimuth_l2}: Azimuth cell annotation.
\code{cell_annotation_blueprint_singler}: SingleR annotation (Blueprint).
\code{cell_annotation_blueprint_monaco}: SingleR annotation (Monaco).
\code{is_immune}: Whether a cell is an immune cell.
\code{sample_heuristic}: Internal sample subdivision helper.
\code{file_id_cellNexus_single_cell}: Internal file id for single-cell layers.
\code{file_id_cellNexus_pseudobulk}: Internal file id for pseudobulk layers.
\code{sample_id}: Harmonised sample identifier.
\code{nCount_RNA}: Total RNA counts per cell (sample-aware).
\code{nFeature_expressed_in_sample}: Number of expressed features per cell.
\code{ethnicity_flagging_score}: Supporting score for ethnicity imputation.
\code{low_confidence_ethnicity}: Supporting flag for low-confidence ethnicity calls.
\code{.aggregated_cells}: Post-QC cells combined into each pseudobulk sample.
\code{imputed_ethnicity}: Imputed ethnicity label.
\code{atlas_id}: cellNexus atlas release identifier (internal use).

